{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place quinoa and water in mixing bowl then cook <nobr>15 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Strain through a fine sieve, discarding liquid then set aside in a bowl to cool.","Place garlic, lemon peel, salt, pepper, spring onions, coriander and parsley in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula then chop again <nobr>3 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>.","Add bread and chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>.","Add cooled quinoa, egg, salmon and capers then mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Using wet hands, shape into 8 patties then place on a large plate. Cover and place in fridge to firm up for at least 30 minutes.","Heat oil in a non-stick frying pan over a medium heat. Fry patties for 3-5 minutes on each side until cooked and golden.","Serve 2 patties per portion, warm, with lemon slices to squeeze over at the table."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["60 g quinoa, red, rinsed","300 g water","1 garlic clove","1 lemon, thin peelings of skin, plus wedges for garnish","½ tsp fine sea salt","2 pinches ground black pepper","20 g spring onions, cut in pieces (1 cm)","6 sprigs fresh coriander, leaves only","6 sprigs fresh parsley, leaves only","80 g bread, torn in pieces","1 medium egg","240 g fresh salmon fillets, skinless, cut in chunks (2 cm)","1 Tbsp pickled capers, drained","olive oil, for frying"]}],"id":"r130234","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-vFUeJMz548o\/XZVRFcU6ROI\/AAAAAAAAdJs\/q9rCL6RmWroQZkajuRJUi3_AKaAP4yPJwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_ehM8Cc_bMvUtUlma.png","title":"Quinoa Salmon Patties","publishedAt":"2017-01-02T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"19.8 g","fat":"14.3 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"20 g","calories":"1204 kJ \/ 288 kcal"},"usefulItems":"cling film, non-stick frying pan, refrigerator, hob","basicInfo":["easy","30m","1h 20m","4 portions"]}